First of all, I'd like to thank Councilor Scott Kelly and Councilor Caviello for being outspoken in their efforts to raise awareness as to what's going on in our schools.

1344
01:47:06,711 --> 01:47:12,475
Neither one of these gentlemen were required to appear for the school committee meeting last night.

1345
01:47:12,695 --> 01:47:20,740
They did so as concerned parents, grandparents, and public servants here in the city.

1346
01:47:21,860 --> 01:47:39,924
And when I listen to what they say, and I listen to what people on the street say, and when I listen to what my kids say, and I listen to what my wife has to say about these public schools as an educator at 25 years in a neighboring school district, it doesn't make me feel good.

1347
01:47:41,105 --> 01:47:42,265
It doesn't make me feel good at all.

1348
01:47:44,165 --> 01:47:46,706
I feel as though we're failing our students.

1349
01:47:48,306 --> 01:47:53,308
We're failing the most vulnerable members of our population, our children.

1350
01:47:55,749 --> 01:47:57,209
Councilor Scott Pelly made a good point.

1351
01:47:58,530 --> 01:48:00,010
He said, it's the one year anniversary.

1352
01:48:00,891 --> 01:48:01,811
I said, one year anniversary?

1353
01:48:01,831 --> 01:48:03,692
Are you talking about one year anniversary or what?

1354
01:48:04,292 --> 01:48:04,972
One year anniversary.

1355
01:48:04,992 --> 01:48:07,293
It's December, Christmas hasn't happened yet.

1356
01:48:07,313 --> 01:48:08,494
I go, one year anniversary or what?

1357
01:48:09,094 --> 01:48:13,275
He goes, no, you don't remember the two walkouts that happened last year?

1358
01:48:15,136 --> 01:48:17,637
The two walkouts at Medford High School that happened last year?

1359
01:48:18,586 --> 01:48:34,553
because of escalating violence in our public schools, when hundreds of children, hundreds of our students, our kids, our neighbors' children, our families got up out of their seats and they walked out of the school because they said, we can't take it anymore.

1360
01:48:34,574 --> 01:48:35,154
We've had enough.

1361
01:48:38,515 --> 01:48:40,176
Here we are exactly one year later.

1362
01:48:42,157 --> 01:48:43,318
I don't think we're in a better place.

1363
01:48:44,978 --> 01:48:46,119
I think we're in a worse place.

1364
01:48:48,134 --> 01:48:49,215
I think we're in a worse place.

1365
01:48:52,177 --> 01:48:55,619
We're in a place where parents are shut out, don't have the opportunity to speak.

1366
01:48:58,401 --> 01:49:00,562
We're in a place where our kids are afraid to go to school.

1367
01:49:01,723 --> 01:49:04,725
And I think we all know what happens when kids become afraid to go to school.

1368
01:49:06,766 --> 01:49:09,228
We've all seen the documentaries on how gangs are formed.

1369
01:49:10,068 --> 01:49:16,653
We've all heard the stories about kids that get bullied in school and then decide to bring weapons because they've had enough and shoot up schools.

1370
01:49:20,170 --> 01:49:22,972
We've all seen this, it's happened in neighboring states.

1371
01:49:23,913 --> 01:49:29,997
Why do we feel as though we're impervious to the same situation or the same circumstances?

1372
01:49:30,017 --> 01:49:31,759
Because we're not, we're not.

1373
01:49:33,740 --> 01:49:35,741
So we're in a place where kids are afraid to go to school.

1374
01:49:37,182 --> 01:49:47,150
And we're also in a place where we see embarrassing news story after embarrassing news story after embarrassing news story in the headlines with the word mentioned.

1375
01:49:48,408 --> 01:49:50,330
And that's a shame because the city is better than that.

1376
01:49:51,711 --> 01:49:52,771
The city is better than that.

1377
01:49:54,353 --> 01:49:55,914
And our kids deserve better than what they're getting.

1378
01:50:00,437 --> 01:50:10,305
There's no accountability that shows it shows in this culture that's permeating our school system is transcending into the classroom.

1379
01:50:12,727 --> 01:50:14,428
And we could all sit here and we can say, this isn't right.

1380
01:50:14,448 --> 01:50:15,109
And this isn't wrong.

1381
01:50:16,215 --> 01:50:17,176
but the data doesn't lie.

1382
01:50:17,536 --> 01:50:18,917
The numbers don't lie.

1383
01:50:19,217 --> 01:50:20,638
So let's talk about the numbers a little bit.

1384
01:50:21,879 --> 01:50:22,920
Let's talk about the numbers.

1385
01:50:22,940 --> 01:50:31,286
42% proficiency in math, 50% proficiency in reading, 240th in the state college readiness index, 181st in graduation rate and 184th overall.

1386
01:50:31,306 --> 01:50:32,166
Our kids deserve better.

1387
01:50:42,074 --> 01:50:43,675
Our kids deserve better than what they get.

1388
01:50:43,695 --> 01:50:46,657
They don't deserve to go to school afraid.

1389
01:50:47,297 --> 01:50:53,021
They deserve to go to school with leaders that are willing to step up and accept the challenge.

1390
01:50:54,302 --> 01:51:04,928
Now, when this incident first happened, I got an email and the email spoke volumes in terms of the culture that's going on with this administration.

1391
01:51:05,089 --> 01:51:08,891
And I have to take a look at it and just mention it because

1392
01:51:09,867 --> 01:51:11,288
I think it really speaks volumes.

1393
01:51:12,228 --> 01:51:14,209
If I can find it and learn how to work this thing.

1394
01:51:26,955 --> 01:51:34,098
This is a confidential and urgent update relative to the circumstances at Medford High School from Dr. Maurice Edward Vincent.

1395
01:51:35,132 --> 01:51:39,694
Our MHS is currently in a stay in place due to a medical emergency.

1396
01:51:40,754 --> 01:51:43,555
A student was stabbed in the restroom and transported to MGH.

1397
01:51:43,655 --> 01:51:45,216
Four students have been identified.

1398
01:51:45,736 --> 01:51:46,916
The police are here working with us.

1399
01:51:47,036 --> 01:51:48,837
We're working on an official communication.

1400
01:51:50,298 --> 01:51:50,938
What's that mean?

1401
01:51:51,638 --> 01:51:53,279
We're working on an official communication.

1402
01:51:54,219 --> 01:51:55,599
You shouldn't have to work on facts.

1403
01:51:55,800 --> 01:51:57,000
You shouldn't have to work on truth.

1404
01:51:57,620 --> 01:52:02,462
You shouldn't have to work on anything other than telling the people what happened and what you're gonna do to prevent it from happening again.

1405
01:52:03,729 --> 01:52:17,020
Here we are 60 days ago, two short months ago, two short months ago, a girl was assaulted, terribly assaulted, captured on video, broadcast all across the local news stations.

1406
01:52:17,400 --> 01:52:20,042
This poor girl has to go to school every day, shake it in her boots.

1407
01:52:20,563 --> 01:52:32,112
If it weren't for the strength of her parents, if it weren't for the strength of her parents coming up here week after week, day after day, fighting to raise awareness about these issues,

1408
01:52:33,480 --> 01:52:34,181
It would have gone away.

1409
01:52:34,801 --> 01:52:38,744
And then 60 days later, we would have been talking about this gentleman that got assaulted and stabbed.

1410
01:52:39,625 --> 01:52:40,746
And then it would have gone away.

1411
01:52:41,967 --> 01:52:43,888
And then 60 days later, something else would happen.

1412
01:52:44,509 --> 01:52:46,791
And we'd bring it up again, and we'd start talking about it.

1413
01:52:47,691 --> 01:52:48,652
Let's get serious about it.

1414
01:52:49,053 --> 01:52:49,313
All right?

1415
01:52:49,853 --> 01:52:50,534
It's been a year.

1416
01:52:51,034 --> 01:52:53,736
It's been a year since the students in that school told us they've had enough.

1417
01:52:54,897 --> 01:52:58,060
It's been a year since they all got up out of their desks and had the courage to walk out.

1418
01:52:58,700 --> 01:52:59,021
All right?

1419
01:52:59,701 --> 01:53:02,023
They had more courage than the adults in the building.

1420
01:53:07,915 --> 01:53:13,298
And now they have to have more courage than the adults in the building to go to school because they're scared for their safety.

1421
01:53:14,659 --> 01:53:15,380
This is sickening.

1422
01:53:16,280 --> 01:53:17,041
This is sickening.

1423
01:53:17,641 --> 01:53:22,884
And nothing anybody can say when they come up to this podium, all right, is gonna change the way I feel about it.

1424
01:53:23,825 --> 01:53:26,667
The way it's been handled is horrible, horrible.

1425
01:53:26,687 --> 01:53:28,128
These aren't isolated incidents.

1426
01:53:28,948 --> 01:53:33,231
A year ago, one year ago, the whole school said we've had enough and they walked out.

1427
01:53:33,851 --> 01:53:36,073
This is not an isolated incident.

1428
01:53:37,031 --> 01:53:43,894
And the longer we keep approaching this situation as an isolated incident, the more isolated incidents are going to occur.

1429
01:53:46,455 --> 01:53:50,056
And then when the budget comes around, we're going to hear the school department cry poor mouth.

1430
01:53:50,556 --> 01:53:53,998
Well, everybody wants to go to Minuteman, and everybody wants to go to the charter school.

1431
01:53:54,018 --> 01:53:54,878
Well, yeah, no kidding.

1432
01:53:55,338 --> 01:53:55,979
Why wouldn't they?

1433
01:53:55,999 --> 01:54:00,781
Then you're going to sign your kid up for karate when they're five years old just to go to Method Eye.

1434
01:54:04,862 --> 01:54:06,503
You can pay one way, or you can pay the other.

1435
01:54:08,024 --> 01:54:15,426
You can pay with peace of mind and financially send them to a school where you feel as though they're going to be safe and you're going to receive what you deserve.

1436
01:54:18,326 --> 01:54:21,367
Or you can take the risks and send them to Medford High.

1437
01:54:21,507 --> 01:54:22,987
And that's what parents are going to say to themselves.

1438
01:54:23,007 --> 01:54:27,208
They're going to say, is it worth it to me to spend this money to not have to put up with stuff like this?

1439
01:54:28,168 --> 01:54:31,369
And parents are going to say yes, because I'm a parent that's thinking about it.

1440
01:54:33,990 --> 01:54:36,210
I'm losing faith in the Medford public school system.

1441
01:54:38,757 --> 01:54:39,597
And I hate to say it.

1442
01:54:40,778 --> 01:54:41,498
I hate to say it.

1443
01:54:42,399 --> 01:54:44,720
Because I went to the Hervey School.

1444
01:54:45,240 --> 01:54:46,401
I went to the Brooks School.

1445
01:54:47,562 --> 01:54:48,782
I went to the Hopps School.

1446
01:54:49,242 --> 01:54:50,443
I went to Medford High School.

1447
01:54:51,063 --> 01:54:52,724
I played sports for Bud Kelly.

1448
01:54:53,024 --> 01:54:55,466
I learned about what it's like to have blue and white in my veins.

1449
01:54:55,946 --> 01:55:00,708
I learned about what it's like to be responsible, to want to be someone that gives back to his community.

1450
01:55:01,689 --> 01:55:03,930
And that's why I chose to seek public office.

1451
01:55:04,570 --> 01:55:05,311
And when I sit here,

1452
01:55:06,603 --> 01:55:10,426
and I watch some of my colleagues in government hide under their desk, it infuriates me.

1453
01:55:12,828 --> 01:55:17,732
It's okay to say no sometimes, you know, and it's okay to say yes, but what you have to do is say something.

1454
01:55:19,453 --> 01:55:23,576
You can't stand for anything if you don't know where you stand and what you stand for.

1455
01:55:26,359 --> 01:55:27,219
Thank you, Madam President.

1456
01:55:28,080 --> 01:55:31,102
Thank you.

1457
01:55:32,503 --> 01:55:33,184
Councillor Collins.

1458
01:55:35,352 --> 01:55:36,192
Thank you, President Morrell.

1459
01:55:36,833 --> 01:55:40,914
Um, you know, mostly right now, I, I want to, I know there are community members in the room.

1460
01:55:40,934 --> 01:55:42,895
I want to hear from community members.

1461
01:55:43,735 --> 01:55:49,258
Um, but I just wanted to say at the outset, you know, yesterday's incident was heartbreaking.

1462
01:55:50,418 --> 01:55:55,400
It's traumatizing during an already extremely raw and difficult time.

1463
01:55:55,420 --> 01:56:00,162
Um, these events affect the whole community as leaders.

1464
01:56:00,242 --> 01:56:02,563
I think it's our responsibility to hear from people who are

1465
01:56:02,997 --> 01:56:05,559
the most affected, the students, the families, teachers and staff.

1466
01:56:05,579 --> 01:56:13,505
I think we can all agree nothing is more important than our public schools being safe and stable and supportive for everybody who has to be inside of them.

1467
01:56:13,525 --> 01:56:15,407
I think that's a really shared goal.

1468
01:56:16,407 --> 01:56:20,451
And I think this heartbreak is shared that our schools are not safe.

1469
01:56:21,031 --> 01:56:21,772
They're not secure.

1470
01:56:21,952 --> 01:56:22,953
They don't feel supportive.

1471
01:56:23,913 --> 01:56:25,915
And, you know, in this conversation,

1472
01:56:26,388 --> 01:56:28,189
You know, I want to hear from the people most affected.

1473
01:56:28,229 --> 01:56:31,190
That's the folks who go to the schools every day and the people who love them.

1474
01:56:32,730 --> 01:56:40,133
As, as we mentioned, you know, many counselors, myself included, have papers later on the agenda for ways that this council can act within its power to try and be part of the solution.

1475
01:56:41,734 --> 01:56:43,395
You know, we'll, we'll get into more of that later.

1476
01:56:44,555 --> 01:56:48,256
It's, it's deeply troubling that we have to be having this conversation.

1477
01:56:48,476 --> 01:56:54,799
I'm just, it's, it's hard to put into words, you know, how to express sympathy for

1478
01:56:55,430 --> 01:56:58,711
something so painful that's happened to kids just going to school and their families.

1479
01:57:00,051 --> 01:57:04,953
It's, you know, it's a sorry thing, the events that precipitated this discussion, but we have to have it and we're gonna have it.

1480
01:57:07,413 --> 01:57:10,414
You know, Councilor Scarpelli and others were calling for urgent action.

1481
01:57:11,054 --> 01:57:14,735
We're calling for the council to act within its purview to try and be part of the solution.

1482
01:57:15,596 --> 01:57:18,456
And I completely agree, completely agree.

1483
01:57:19,157 --> 01:57:22,197
You know, we have to use our powers as city councilors to try and be part of the solution.

1484
01:57:23,138 --> 01:57:24,438
We aren't the school committee.

1485
01:57:25,147 --> 01:57:26,148
We can't be the school committee.

1486
01:57:26,748 --> 01:57:30,050
We can't make the type of the decisions that the school committee is empowered to make.

1487
01:57:30,890 --> 01:57:44,018
We can use the powers that we have as the city council to try to direct resources where they need to go, to try to be a part of the community-wide conversation, to emphasize the voices of the folks that are most affected by this, to listen to the people who know best where those resources need to go.

1488
01:57:45,118 --> 01:57:47,840
And I'm glad that we get to be a part of that conversation.

1489
01:57:47,880 --> 01:57:51,742
I hope that going forward, this can be more collaborative

1490
01:57:52,073 --> 01:57:55,395
that we can all do our specific roles, but in concert with each other.

1491
01:57:55,415 --> 01:58:06,480
And lastly, since Councilor Scarpelli's resolution calls for public input, if anybody's here to give input, I just want to acknowledge that not everybody does feel comfortable speaking in public, especially on live TV.

1492
01:58:06,520 --> 01:58:07,481
It's not for the faint of heart.

1493
01:58:08,221 --> 01:58:14,804
And also not every comment, especially when kids and school security is involved, is best said in a public setting.

1494
01:58:15,425 --> 01:58:20,267
I just want to restate for the record, whether we're in session or not, I'm available.

1495
01:58:20,899 --> 01:58:26,023
to any resident, to any constituent, to field ideas, to hear your questions.

1496
01:58:26,083 --> 01:58:31,608
If you just need a listening ear, if you don't feel comfortable speaking tonight, you can always reach out to me.

1497
01:58:32,149 --> 01:58:33,029
We're available.

1498
01:58:34,090 --> 01:58:37,993
So I just wanted to say that at the outset of any community input.

1499
01:58:38,234 --> 01:58:38,614
Thank you.

1500
01:58:39,275 --> 01:58:40,956
Thank you, Councilor Collins.

1501
01:58:40,976 --> 01:58:41,917
Vice President Behrs.

1502
01:58:43,658 --> 01:58:44,479
Thank you, Madam President.

1503
01:58:47,041 --> 01:58:48,002
Nobody's happy.

1504
01:58:49,992 --> 01:58:51,753
There's disagreements about this.

1505
01:58:52,514 --> 01:58:54,255
I don't think there's any single person.

1506
01:58:54,275 --> 01:58:58,999
And if there is, they got to get checked out who was happy about what happened yesterday.

1507
01:58:59,019 --> 01:59:14,152
I think everyone agrees and agreed six months ago, or two months ago, or two days ago, that there are things that need to be improved, that there are problems that need to be solved, that we're not

1508
01:59:15,640 --> 01:59:23,542
always, and even if we had solved them, that we're not always going to get it 100% right 100% of the time.

1509
01:59:27,063 --> 01:59:37,165
Now, how we address those problems, how we build processes, how we improve systems, how we address systemic challenges, is by putting forward solutions.

1510
01:59:39,006 --> 01:59:44,947
The thing that we're talking about in resolutions coming later than this are some ideas around that.

1511
01:59:47,291 --> 02:00:13,504
But I think also it's important to look back at what we've heard from our school committee and school administration, what we've heard from this council, when it comes to the budget and the funding of our schools, when it comes to the resources that we need, when it comes to the resources that we need in this moment, when we know, hey, there was violence at Medford High School when I was there.

1512
02:00:14,064 --> 02:00:15,905
There was violence at Medford High School 30 years ago.

1513
02:00:16,809 --> 02:00:18,150
And we can talk about certain numbers.

1514
02:00:18,590 --> 02:00:23,114
The one number that hasn't been talked about any of this is actually looking at the trends and data on this issue.

1515
02:00:24,435 --> 02:00:35,263
But the one thing we do know is whether it's Medford or a neighboring community or every community in Massachusetts or every community in this country is that student supports are deeply needed.

1516
02:00:35,523 --> 02:00:37,585
That mental health is a serious issue.

1517
02:00:37,925 --> 02:00:43,849
That conflict resolution and addressing problems in a peaceful manner is a huge problem.

1518
02:00:44,610 --> 02:00:45,991
And that quite frankly,

1519
02:00:47,172 --> 02:00:49,933
Before these things got worse, it was a problem.

1520
02:00:50,134 --> 02:00:51,714
It's an even worse problem now.

1521
02:00:52,195 --> 02:00:54,276
Students are walking out because they recognize it.

1522
02:00:54,696 --> 02:00:58,538
Students are crying out because they know that they need help or they know someone who needs help.

1523
02:00:59,438 --> 02:01:00,639
It's a question of resources.

1524
02:01:01,879 --> 02:01:06,402
The first thing I thought about when I ran for office was the funding for our schools three years ago, that was before the pandemic.

1525
02:01:06,942 --> 02:01:15,166
It was my first concern in June when we were talking about the fiscal 23 budget and the $2.8 million that got cut from our schools at the last minute.

1526
02:01:17,263 --> 02:01:27,792
two weeks ago, it was again, where I was focusing my energy and efforts in a resolution that passed this council about funding and asking what are the supports?

1527
02:01:27,812 --> 02:01:28,973
What are the funding that's needed?

1528
02:01:30,574 --> 02:01:35,338
Another thing that needs resources and funding, we were just talking about it for municipal vulnerability plan.

1529
02:01:35,378 --> 02:01:36,359
We're just talking about it.

1530
02:01:37,379 --> 02:01:45,386
When we talk about this whole city, schools and city side communications and engagement, the city doesn't invest its budgetary resources in that issue.

1531
02:01:45,906 --> 02:01:46,527
So we have

1532
02:01:47,922 --> 02:01:52,645
you know, people scrambling to put something together to get it out when there's an emergency situation.

1533
02:01:53,345 --> 02:02:00,429
We have in a million other situations insufficient resources for communication and engagement.

1534
02:02:02,130 --> 02:02:05,212
So all of these things, no one is happy here.

1535
02:02:06,092 --> 02:02:08,714
We've all identified problems that we want to solve.

1536
02:02:09,214 --> 02:02:11,075
We're starting to talk about solutions.

1537
02:02:11,836 --> 02:02:15,418
The big elephant in the room solution that we don't want to zone in on

1538
02:02:16,062 --> 02:02:19,603
is that we don't have the resources to address the scope of the problems that we have.

1539
02:02:20,443 --> 02:02:40,127
And until we are willing to admit that and engage in a good faith discussion about what is the true scope of resources that we need to invest in our schools and in our community to address the sheer scale of the problems that we have, we're not going to unify or come together or solve these issues.

1540
02:02:41,027 --> 02:02:45,008
And they are of a scope and scale we could not have imagined four years ago.

1541
02:02:46,065 --> 02:02:49,228
So that's the crux of this whole question.

1542
02:02:50,129 --> 02:02:56,355
We come together in government to pool our resources to address our collective problems.

1543
02:02:56,795 --> 02:02:59,458
That is what we do more than anything else.

1544
02:03:00,278 --> 02:03:09,247
And we've clearly identified a collective problem that needs resources and the resources, we are literally unable to put those resources on the table.

1545
02:03:10,396 --> 02:03:25,389
Now, I think there are things that we can do and should do and try to do in the short term, medium and long term with what we have to better target what we have and do the best that we can do with what we have, but that's not going to be enough.

1546
02:03:27,951 --> 02:03:34,737
The other two things I want to talk about here are that we are once again, not going to

1547
02:03:35,216 --> 02:03:49,404
get unified and be on the same page and be able to move forward collectively, unless we are moving on a single set of facts about who has the authority to do what, who has the power to do what, and who sets the rules about what.

1548
02:03:50,705 --> 02:04:00,290
