1559
02:05:15,546 --> 02:05:23,329
So, you know, I know that that's the nicest way that I can think of to say what I really wanna say here.

1560
02:05:23,889 --> 02:05:25,790
But when we talk about unity,

1561
02:05:27,384 --> 02:05:30,146
we can't then have the next sentence be something that divides.

1562
02:05:31,907 --> 02:05:50,479
And I think, again, the thing that we can unify around here, maybe it's not the most heartwarming thing to unify around here, is that nobody is happy, there are problems, and we need to identify and move forward on solutions to those problems.

1563
02:05:50,619 --> 02:05:55,062
And I think if we can do that and accept a single set of facts about

1564
02:05:55,855 --> 02:06:07,218
what is truly going on, then we are laying the foundation to have the substantive conversations and make the real actions that we need so that kids in our schools feel safe.

1565
02:06:07,958 --> 02:06:09,878
I know what it was like to not feel safe.

1566
02:06:10,519 --> 02:06:16,520
I stayed home for a whole week from school because I didn't want to get on the bus because I was attacked when I was in middle school, okay?

1567
02:06:16,580 --> 02:06:21,301
And I'm not even equating that to what happened on Monday or what happened to other people, right?

1568
02:06:21,321 --> 02:06:24,122
I experienced that in my family.

1569
02:06:25,447 --> 02:06:44,731
So we can say that there's a monopoly on the feelings here, but we know what we know and we know that what we have to put forward is not sufficient at this moment to address the scope of the challenge that we face.

1570
02:06:45,271 --> 02:06:51,973
And I think the best thing that we can do is to look at the resolutions before us that are solutions focused and ask

1571
02:06:52,940 --> 02:07:10,415
the people most affected the students and teachers on the ground to work with the school committee and the mayor and the school administration and the city council to figure out what we can do in the short term to address funding and what we can do in the long term to make a systemic solution and a systemic approach to make sure that

1572
02:07:10,808 --> 02:07:23,035
we're addressing this issue in two weeks, in two months, in two years, and in two decades, because we heard last night that there were people who felt that 30 years ago to today, things hadn't been fixed.

1573
02:07:23,395 --> 02:07:25,497
So that's all I wanna say on this.

1574
02:07:25,597 --> 02:07:27,838
Beyond that, I'm not gonna speak to this paper anymore.

1575
02:07:28,258 --> 02:07:33,601
I'll speak to the solutions-focused resolutions that we have next, and I'll leave it at that.

1576
02:07:33,641 --> 02:07:34,482
Thank you, Madam President.

1577
02:07:34,622 --> 02:07:34,882
Thank you.

