This hurts.

1590
02:08:25,048 --> 02:08:26,649
This hurts emotionally.

1591
02:08:26,669 --> 02:08:30,872
It hurts physically.

1592
02:08:30,972 --> 02:08:32,513
It's important to deal with it.

1593
02:08:32,873 --> 02:08:33,713
And it matters.

1594
02:08:34,054 --> 02:08:35,074
It matters to all of us.

1595
02:08:35,154 --> 02:08:38,116
And look, everyone, everyone,

1596
02:08:39,613 --> 02:08:47,477
in this room, everyone online on Zoom is upset, is frustrated, is saddened.

1597
02:08:49,258 --> 02:09:02,286
And I think we all feel sympathy for the experience that our students have had to deal with and continue to have to deal with at Medford High School.

1598
02:09:03,526 --> 02:09:06,148
I will say I am relieved to hear

1599
02:09:06,894 --> 02:09:13,755
that the student is in stable condition, but that doesn't mean that everything is over.

1600
02:09:16,496 --> 02:09:24,158
I really appreciate the talk from counselors of all backgrounds about the importance of finding solutions.

1601
02:09:25,858 --> 02:09:35,880
And I think to that effect, I wanna thank President Morrell and Vice President Behrs for opening up the city council agenda to allow us to put resolutions on the agenda to have this conversation tonight.

1602
02:09:36,740 --> 02:09:45,412
And to allow us to act fast and to allow us to have this conversation tonight to my parents in the room on in on zoom.

1603
02:09:47,934 --> 02:09:54,338
Look, school violence, and I've said this before, and it's in the news, there's tons of research out there.

1604
02:09:54,979 --> 02:09:57,080
It's an international problem.

1605
02:09:57,260 --> 02:09:58,281
It's a domestic problem.

1606
02:09:58,441 --> 02:09:59,382
It's a Medford problem.

1607
02:10:00,783 --> 02:10:03,505
And that actually means that we have to deal with it.

1608
02:10:03,585 --> 02:10:05,346
And we do have to address it here at home.

1609
02:10:06,827 --> 02:10:10,069
School violence has been around for a while.

1610
02:10:11,190 --> 02:10:13,892
Councilor Behrs has spoken to his experience.

1611
02:10:15,057 --> 02:10:16,978
I went to Medford High School just five years ago.

1612
02:10:17,259 --> 02:10:21,161
I know what it's like there.

1613
02:10:21,221 --> 02:10:23,523
And it's a wonderful institution to learn.

1614
02:10:24,043 --> 02:10:26,225
There are blemishes on it as well.

1615
02:10:27,005 --> 02:10:39,034
And this work, these are all issues that school leaders, teachers, students, everyone has been working together to address over the last few years.

1616
02:10:39,514 --> 02:10:42,236
And it's evident that we need to put even more energy towards it.

1617
02:10:43,757 --> 02:10:53,202
And as I've said before as well, until our schools are safe for everyone, for all, we still have more work to do.

1618
02:10:53,863 --> 02:11:00,186
We need to find sustainable solutions, and that means engaging stakeholders from students to parents to teachers.

1619
02:11:00,826 --> 02:11:10,972
I know people aren't gonna like this, but the school committee who have been elected to govern our schools, to oversee our schools, and we need to engage school leaders as well.

1620
02:11:12,002 --> 02:11:17,624
We need to enforce the existing policies on violence and on anti-bullying.

1621
02:11:18,404 --> 02:11:22,286
And we need accountability to make sure that we're enforcing these policies.

1622
02:11:23,926 --> 02:11:33,270
We need to think through the actions that we can take to protect all kids carefully.

1623
02:11:34,155 --> 02:11:42,180
and quickly, I will add, but we need to make sure that they're equitable and reasonable and that they really truly do protect every kid in the classroom and in the hallways.

1624
02:11:44,141 --> 02:12:02,513
I think it's also evidence that there's a major communications problem that we as a city council have been bringing up in the city, the communications problem in the city when it comes to not just in an incident like this, but just in general, getting the message out to residents.

1625
02:12:03,288 --> 02:12:09,212
But when it comes to this incident as well, we need to know.

1626
02:12:09,393 --> 02:12:13,536
And I think President Morrell and I have written a resolution to this effect.

1627
02:12:14,857 --> 02:12:16,998
We need to know about the incident.

1628
02:12:17,018 --> 02:12:18,039
We need to know the details.

1629
02:12:18,059 --> 02:12:20,961
We need to know authority and rules and who has authority over what.

1630
02:12:22,182 --> 02:12:24,584
And we need to prevent misinformation from being spread.

1631
02:12:26,909 --> 02:12:36,778
And school committee members at yesterday's meeting have also acknowledged that as a city, we need to do better on communications and on engaging families as well.

1632
02:12:39,300 --> 02:12:40,301
Councillor Behrs is right.

1633
02:12:40,602 --> 02:12:41,883
The funding problem is real.

1634
02:12:42,003 --> 02:12:47,969
It's one of the reasons why I decided to run for office in the first place, watching the budget conversation years ago when

1635
02:12:49,190 --> 02:12:54,232
We made major cuts to guidance and to mental health and counseling at our schools.

1636
02:12:54,853 --> 02:12:56,333
And now we're seeing the effects of it.

1637
02:12:57,894 --> 02:13:00,735
We need to be serious about that.

1638
02:13:00,855 --> 02:13:05,237
We need to be serious about funding and to realize that there is a funding issue.

1639
02:13:05,978 --> 02:13:13,701
And that effect, that problem is trickling down to our hallways and to our classrooms.

1640
02:13:17,162 --> 02:13:28,050
and that particularly after COVID and after remote learning, there has been an epidemic of poor mental health in the city and in this country.

1641
02:13:28,070 --> 02:13:44,883
I asked the city and the city council joined me in passing a resolution months ago, asking the city to do a general survey on youth mental health and to look at the effects of that and to see what we can do to invest more in it and to prevent

1642
02:13:45,504 --> 02:13:47,046
things like this from happening.

1643
02:13:47,847 --> 02:13:52,493
And it is upsetting as a counselor to see that we haven't done enough on it.

1644
02:13:54,035 --> 02:13:59,302
This council has been responsible in doing that and we have been proactive in addressing youth mental health.

1645
02:14:01,518 --> 02:14:04,860
I want us to do as much as possible, as quickly as possible.

1646
02:14:05,921 --> 02:14:09,624
I think that's something that everyone behind the reel would agree on.

1647
02:14:11,005 --> 02:14:15,829
But I also do wanna make sure that we are creating lasting solutions within our purview.

1648
02:14:16,449 --> 02:14:27,658
I know not everyone will agree with my approach on this issue and my ideas, but I am open-minded to hear more ideas, to hear feedback, both positive and negative.

1649
02:14:29,058 --> 02:14:49,608
And I understand, as Councilor Collins has mentioned, that many members of our community weren't able to make it to this meeting for scheduling reasons, for family reasons, and many members of our community aren't joining us today because they're afraid to talk and talking in public is not for everyone.

1650
02:14:49,628 --> 02:14:56,531
And to those people, my inbox and my voicemail box and my text message inbox is also open to everyone.

1651
02:14:58,133 --> 02:15:15,800
I think it's really important to emphasize that regardless of the tone of this conversation, regardless of the points that people have brought up, regardless of the feedback that we're going to hear, and I think people in our community, there are many, many different ways of thinking about this issue and about the solutions for this issue.

1652
02:15:16,640 --> 02:15:20,302
I think that's been evident to me in the conversations that I've had.

1653
02:15:20,777 --> 02:15:24,359
with neighbors, with residents, with young folks in the last 24 hours.

1654
02:15:25,919 --> 02:15:45,548
I think it's important to acknowledge the differences, but to also acknowledge the points of unity that I think we see on this agenda tonight, because those points of unity, those are the seeds, I think, for more lasting, more substantive policy changes in the future that will better, I think, create a school environment for our children.

1655
02:15:47,409 --> 02:15:48,129
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

1656
02:15:48,369 --> 02:15:49,009
Councilor Scarpelli.

1657
02:15:49,570 --> 02:15:50,370
Thank you, Madam President.

1658
02:15:53,885 --> 02:16:03,012
trying to be restrained and understanding something very simple that I want to share with my fellow counselors that gave their opinions.

1659
02:16:04,073 --> 02:16:04,974
Agree to disagree.

1660
02:16:05,574 --> 02:16:06,695
We've done that many times.

1661
02:16:11,279 --> 02:16:12,240
These are our children.

1662
02:16:13,401 --> 02:16:14,321
They're unsafe.

1663
02:16:14,902 --> 02:16:15,783
They're scared.

1664
02:16:16,803 --> 02:16:18,345
Our teachers are scared.

1665
02:16:21,206 --> 02:16:27,409
to talk about money concerns and money issues should not be even a thought right now.

1666
02:16:29,070 --> 02:16:39,034
The thought and the discussion of 30 years ago, five years ago, is an embarrassment to me for the fact that this is happening.

1667
02:16:39,415 --> 02:16:42,236
This is happening right now.

1668
02:16:44,757 --> 02:16:50,420
When I talk about unifying, I talk about what I said as a national agenda.

1669
02:16:52,155 --> 02:17:00,080
we see and hear the direction that the school committee has gone on many different levels.

1670
02:17:01,161 --> 02:17:13,649
And some school committees, members have called me in the past and just didn't understand that they wouldn't fight if they didn't have their own voice, but to follow this national agenda.

1671
02:17:15,150 --> 02:17:15,931
And as I'm seeing,

1672
02:17:16,975 --> 02:17:38,927
the people that I looked at and trusted and admired, I'm seeing that they're taking not what's important today in our schools, not what's important, our children, not their safety, but to be in this council chamber yesterday and listen to some of these people that truly are aligned with people in this room.

1673
02:17:41,989 --> 02:17:46,111
So these issues are concerning to the community to understand

1674
02:17:47,397 --> 02:17:48,997
that we need to put that away.

1675
02:17:51,058 --> 02:17:57,759
Open our minds and be unified in the fact that the unification is needed for the safety of our children.

1676
02:17:58,439 --> 02:17:59,940
Not what happened five years ago.

1677
02:18:00,820 --> 02:18:02,160
Not what happened 30 years ago.

1678
02:18:03,120 --> 02:18:04,101
What's happening today.

1679
02:18:04,121 --> 02:18:07,661
We're not gonna get the funding we need.

1680
02:18:07,721 --> 02:18:08,322
We know that.

1681
02:18:08,642 --> 02:18:10,042
And that's not gonna change.

1682
02:18:10,082 --> 02:18:14,503
So bringing that up right now is really sad to me.

1683
02:18:15,447 --> 02:18:18,008
That's just a buzzword and a check off.

1684
02:18:19,909 --> 02:18:23,070
So I will tell you, we need movement now.

