1698
02:19:41,667 --> 02:19:43,648
I was questioned that I was part of that school committee.

1699
02:19:45,008 --> 02:19:46,028
And there are legalities.

1700
02:19:47,609 --> 02:19:48,969
And I understood those legalities.

1701
02:19:50,129 --> 02:19:50,709
But you know what?

1702
02:19:51,249 --> 02:19:54,930
When it came to children's safety, George Scott Pelley never swayed.

1703
02:19:55,350 --> 02:19:56,571
I made sure that they were safe.

1704
02:19:58,151 --> 02:20:00,892
I never had this situation when I was on the school committee.

1705
02:20:01,392 --> 02:20:01,832
Thank God.

1706
02:20:04,102 --> 02:20:13,327
But I will tell you, we can bicker back and forth and disagree, but ultimately, that wasn't my intention today.

1707
02:20:13,927 --> 02:20:17,869
My intention is truly look at everybody and say, let's meet now.

1708
02:20:18,330 --> 02:20:19,831
Let's bring everybody together now.

1709
02:20:20,231 --> 02:20:25,894
Let's set a plan that's tangible that we can reach, that we're not gonna get grants from the state.

1710
02:20:25,934 --> 02:20:33,398
We're not gonna get funding from City Hall, but there's ways to get that done right now to make our children feel safe.

1711
02:20:34,915 --> 02:20:35,195
Thank you.

1712
02:20:40,837 --> 02:20:43,197
Any further discussion from the council at this time?

1713
02:20:43,317 --> 02:20:44,218
Madam President, if I may.

1714
02:20:44,458 --> 02:20:45,458
Councillor Nye.

1715
02:20:45,618 --> 02:20:46,258
Thank you very much.

1716
02:20:46,278 --> 02:20:54,360
You know, there's no such thing as a utopian society.

1717
02:20:56,341 --> 02:21:03,223
And I don't think in this instance that throwing money at an issue, and quite frankly,

1718
02:21:03,997 --> 02:21:10,678
given the decision makers who aren't allocating funds properly in the first place, more money to spend.

1719
02:21:10,698 --> 02:21:16,300
I don't think this is going to do anything for those children that need to go to school tomorrow.

1720
02:21:17,400 --> 02:21:23,121
It might help in the long run, but it's not going to do anything for those children that need to go to school tomorrow.

1721
02:21:26,302 --> 02:21:29,642
What this is about is reallocation.

1722
02:21:31,883 --> 02:21:32,503
As of right now,

1723
02:21:33,762 --> 02:21:38,706
The committee needs to live within its means because there is no funding request from the mayor before us.

1724
02:21:39,767 --> 02:21:41,588
So we can jump up and down and say, we want more money.

1725
02:21:41,648 --> 02:21:42,189
We want more money.

1726
02:21:42,209 --> 02:21:43,630
We do that every week about every issue.

1727
02:21:44,670 --> 02:21:59,442
But ultimately right now, the administration hasn't put the paper before this body, which tells me the administration isn't taking it seriously, which would again, move me to the position to say, you have to live within your means and reallocate your funds then to address this issue.

1728
02:21:59,502 --> 02:22:00,743
So what's the plan and what are you going to do?

1729
02:22:02,013 --> 02:22:07,455
And why are our kids going back to school tomorrow if you don't have a plan and you don't know what you're gonna do?

1730
02:22:08,295 --> 02:22:11,357
Quite frankly, I think the school should have been shut down until after Christmas vacation.

1731
02:22:12,637 --> 02:22:15,778
Blanket, sorry, high school's closed until after Christmas vacation.

1732
02:22:16,559 --> 02:22:21,681
In the interest of safety, in the interest of us showing this community that we're serious about the issues that are before us.

1733
02:22:22,541 --> 02:22:24,862
Because a year has gone by and we haven't showed that.

1734
02:22:28,803 --> 02:22:29,624
So, you know,

1735
02:22:31,198 --> 02:22:50,268
Certainly someone that recognizes that there's a need for resources, but I also think that there is room for reallocation of existing funds, existing policies, and existing practices that will improve the safety in our schools.

1736
02:22:51,169 --> 02:22:55,471
Reversing some of the policy decisions that were made over the last year is a good start.

1737
02:22:59,348 --> 02:23:04,150
But again, there's no such thing as a utopian society and there's never going to be enough.

1738
02:23:04,510 --> 02:23:05,230
How much is enough?

1739
02:23:06,111 --> 02:23:07,071
There's never going to be enough.

1740
02:23:07,691 --> 02:23:09,752
There's never, we're never going to reach a point where we say, Oh, we're cool.

1741
02:23:10,052 --> 02:23:10,533
This is good.

1742
02:23:10,753 --> 02:23:12,613
This is enough money for us to do whatever we need to do.

1743
02:23:13,274 --> 02:23:13,514
All right.

1744
02:23:13,614 --> 02:23:14,314
That doesn't happen.

1745
02:23:15,435 --> 02:23:16,175
That doesn't happen.

1746
02:23:16,255 --> 02:23:19,016
Nobody says, I want to make less money next year than I made this year.

1747
02:23:19,536 --> 02:23:20,577
That's just not the way it works.

1748
02:23:21,417 --> 02:23:25,599
So, you know, we can keep throwing money at issues or we can say, where are you allocating this money?

1749
02:23:25,639 --> 02:23:26,359
And is this a good plan?

1750
02:23:27,125 --> 02:23:28,846
Because throwing money at issues doesn't do anything.

1751
02:23:28,866 --> 02:23:31,187
It's not going to fix the problem if we're not spending it in the right place.

1752
02:23:31,527 --> 02:23:34,668
And it's clear that the money we've already provided isn't being spent in the right place.

1753
02:23:35,449 --> 02:23:37,350
So maybe it comes down to a reallocation plan.

1754
02:23:37,630 --> 02:23:41,752
And then what can we do to supplement that reallocation plan, but let them live with the existing means that they have?

1755
02:23:42,292 --> 02:23:49,395
Because quite frankly, it seems like every time something comes up, they just, anything in this community, quite frankly, anytime anything comes up, it's, we don't have any money.

1756
02:23:49,755 --> 02:23:50,716
We don't have any money to do it.

1757
02:23:50,756 --> 02:23:51,696
We don't have any money to do it.

1758
02:23:52,882 --> 02:23:56,425
All right, well, if you don't have any money to do it and it needs to get done, then what's the next thing you got to do?

1759
02:23:56,485 --> 02:23:57,846
You got to reallocate.

1760
02:23:58,567 --> 02:24:00,269
You got to change your game plan up a little bit there, folks.

1761
02:24:00,349 --> 02:24:00,829
You know what I mean?

1762
02:24:01,450 --> 02:24:04,352
It's like Belichick at halftime, you know, change the game plan, win the game.

1763
02:24:05,173 --> 02:24:07,335
We're not changing the game plan at halftime.

1764
02:24:07,515 --> 02:24:17,464
We're not taking a real strong self-assessment as to where we stand and then making adjustments to improve our position.

1765
02:24:20,790 --> 02:24:23,871
I'll be short, the game is rigged.

1766
02:24:25,491 --> 02:24:27,832
We can try to change our game plan as much as we want.

1767
02:24:28,212 --> 02:24:35,634
But when we're talking about city departments and city budgets that in real inflation adjusted dollar terms have less money now than they did in 1980, the game is rigged.

1768
02:24:37,114 --> 02:24:37,895
So that's the first thing.

1769
02:24:38,095 --> 02:24:45,957
I'm not disputing that there are things we could do immediately to bring people together and try to find solutions.

1770
02:24:45,977 --> 02:24:47,477
I think that's exactly what we have on here tonight.

1771
02:24:48,499 --> 02:24:52,540
There are things we could do with short money that could make a big impact and make people feel safer.

1772
02:24:52,560 --> 02:24:53,861
And I think that's what we're asking for.

1773
02:24:54,401 --> 02:25:13,348
But I think the idea that we can fix this whole problem, or that the notion of putting more resources, this is just throwing money at the problem, that we can address a problem that has been persistent, that is growing in scale, that is not just unique to Medford, even though we could do what we can in Medford to find unique solutions with what we have through reallocation and additional resources.

1774
02:25:15,175 --> 02:25:17,977
it's promising something that's unachievable.

1775
02:25:18,838 --> 02:25:24,541
So I agree, let's do what we can now with short money or no money at all to make people feel safer in the schools.

1776
02:25:24,681 --> 02:25:26,562
I completely understand and respect that.

1777
02:25:27,182 --> 02:25:28,343
And I think we have to do that.

1778
02:25:29,043 --> 02:25:36,688
But if we're not, again, if we're not thinking about this in a bigger terms of, you know, when we talk about resources, yeah,

1779
02:25:37,220 --> 02:25:43,262
make people feel safer, I would bet to have some additional resources around the hallways and the bathrooms, because that's clearly been a problem.

1780
02:25:43,322 --> 02:25:45,943
It was a problem that came up before what happened yesterday.

1781
02:25:46,543 --> 02:25:47,904
Obviously it was a problem yesterday.

1782
02:25:47,964 --> 02:25:49,624
That's something that'll make people feel safer.

1783
02:25:50,004 --> 02:25:52,265
And we can figure out ways to target resources to do that.

1784
02:25:53,525 --> 02:26:06,310
But when we talk about students' mental health and the mental health crisis and the fact that we need dozens of more counselors at our school, or we need to bring back maybe an assistant principal at the high school, or we have to look at the funding cuts that were made in 2020,

1785
02:26:07,582 --> 02:26:08,442
or 2023.

1786
02:26:09,842 --> 02:26:25,826
Those are big ticket items that, you know, if we just want to say we'll never get there, then all we're going to do is the short money things that make people feel a little bit safer until they don't work anymore, or until more kids are facing issues with mental health and conflict resolution.

1787
02:26:26,506 --> 02:26:29,427
I'm going to stop there, because I don't think it's mutually exclusive.

1788
02:26:29,947 --> 02:26:34,828
I'm not saying we can only do one piece of it and not the other and I don't think anyone else is saying the other way around.

1789
02:26:36,387 --> 02:26:52,936
If we don't have that conversation and admit that, we're not going to be operating on a set of facts and under the urgency that we need to be operating under to bring the solutions to bear that we obviously all agree need to be brought to bear.

1790
02:26:52,956 --> 02:26:54,097
Thank you.

1791
02:26:54,357 --> 02:26:54,937
Councilor Collins.

1792
02:26:56,498 --> 02:26:57,478
Thank you, President Morrell.

1793
02:26:57,518 --> 02:26:59,680
And I'm speaking off the cuff here.

1794
02:26:59,720 --> 02:27:03,962
So I just wanna say, I think that what the community deserves

1795
02:27:05,088 --> 02:27:11,229
today in the aftermath of yesterday's events, in the aftermath of other traumatic, tragic events.

1796
02:27:11,450 --> 02:27:20,352
What the community deserves is a communicative, collaborative city council.

1797
02:27:20,752 --> 02:27:27,693
They deserve clear communication, resolve to work together productively from all their elected leaders.

1798
02:27:28,714 --> 02:27:30,534
We owe our community better than infighting.

1799
02:27:31,234 --> 02:27:34,495
You know, we've disagreed on many things many times before,

1800
02:27:35,258 --> 02:27:37,759
Behind this rail, it'll happen again.

1801
02:27:38,139 --> 02:27:39,280
That's what we're here to do.

1802
02:27:40,200 --> 02:27:43,821
We're here to represent different viewpoints for perspective on issues.

1803
02:27:43,841 --> 02:27:50,744
We're here to represent different viewpoints for how to craft strategy and how to respond to problems in our community and how to plan for the future.

1804
02:27:51,964 --> 02:28:04,049
But I think that we owe today, especially today and all days, we owe the community a productive use of our time, discussing available strategies for what we can do within our powers

1805
02:28:04,502 --> 02:28:06,523
to try to deal with the problems before us.

1806
02:28:07,364 --> 02:28:25,996
I, you know, what, what looks like a buzzword to one counselor might be somebody else's best good faith, earnest approach at doing something that is within our power, within our purview to try to address specifically a problem that exists.

1807
02:28:26,596 --> 02:28:27,797
It's put forth in good faith.

1808
02:28:27,897 --> 02:28:29,218
And I think that tracks both ways.

1809
02:28:29,358 --> 02:28:32,080
I don't think it's productive for us to launch into

1810
02:28:35,190 --> 02:28:36,791
veiled personal attacks.

1811
02:28:38,232 --> 02:28:39,813
I don't want that to be what tonight is.

1812
02:28:39,833 --> 02:28:41,394
I think that we have to come together.

1813
02:28:41,715 --> 02:28:43,916
We have to discuss the strategies that we've put forth.

1814
02:28:44,236 --> 02:28:50,181
We might not agree on all of them, but what our community is calling out for is a good faith, earnest discussion of strategies.

1815
02:28:51,241 --> 02:29:01,488
It does our community no good to spill a lot of ink and spill a lot of airtime, fighting about things that we cannot control.

1816
02:29:01,749 --> 02:29:03,550
The community deserves better than a performance.

1817
02:29:04,091 --> 02:29:07,493
we need to discuss strategies that we have the capacity to enforce.

1818
02:29:07,973 --> 02:29:12,135
And sometimes we will disagree about what those best strategies are, but that's what our time should be for.

1819
02:29:12,536 --> 02:29:18,519
So I have a rationale for why I brought the strategies that I think are most important to talk about here.

1820
02:29:18,539 --> 02:29:20,700
I know those feelings aren't universally shared.

1821
02:29:20,720 --> 02:29:25,523
I'll save that for when those papers are brought up, but I really hope that we can maintain just

1822
02:29:26,579 --> 02:29:33,963
clear communication and sticking to the issues at hand and striving for concrete strategies for as much of this evening as possible, because that's what the community needs from us.

1823
02:29:34,284 --> 02:29:34,564
Thank you.

1824
02:29:34,584 --> 02:29:36,665
Thank you, Councillor Collins.

1825
02:29:36,765 --> 02:29:40,507
And I do believe the intent of the resolution is to open it up for public participation.

1826
02:29:40,527 --> 02:29:43,449
So I want to see if there's any further discussion from the council, but I want to make sure

1827
02:29:44,082 --> 02:29:45,182
we move forward to that.

1828
02:29:45,682 --> 02:29:50,724
Seeing none, I just want to just briefly, Councilor Scarpelli, I absolutely hear your calls for unity.

1829
02:29:50,744 --> 02:29:51,964
I hear everyone's calls for unity.

1830
02:29:52,064 --> 02:29:58,446
And I believe that the council is absolutely unified and that no one wanted yesterday to happen.

1831
02:29:58,966 --> 02:30:01,347
No one wanted the incident two months ago to happen.

1832
02:30:01,427 --> 02:30:04,968
No one wanted any student to get hurt in our schools ever.

1833
02:30:05,848 --> 02:30:06,868
Schools should be a refuge.

1834
02:30:07,108 --> 02:30:12,690
We talk about a lot of these issues go beyond the schools, that a lot of these issues start at home because of course they do.

1835
02:30:13,208 --> 02:30:17,750
but every student deserves the opportunity to go to school and feel safe.

1836
02:30:17,870 --> 02:30:23,593
And I know every member of this council, every person in the chambers, every person on Zoom, I know they feel that.

1837
02:30:24,373 --> 02:30:38,320
So I hope that we can continue to have this talk and come to solutions so that students can feel safe, so that parents can feel comfortable sending their kids to school, and so that teachers can have the space to do their jobs and do what they do best.

1838
02:30:39,519 --> 02:30:41,340
So I'm going to open it up to public participation.

1839
02:30:42,001 --> 02:30:46,284
Before we go to that, I do just want to note public participation is just that, it is to hear from the public.

1840
02:30:46,464 --> 02:30:47,584
It is not meant to be a debate.

1841
02:30:48,805 --> 02:30:51,627
No personal tax will be permitted.

1842
02:30:51,647 --> 02:30:56,530
I will gavel them and no speculation that will further engage your students will be allowed either.

1843
02:30:57,331 --> 02:30:58,412
So opening it up.

1844
02:31:04,376 --> 02:31:07,218
Seeing Madam Superintendent and Member McLaughlin.

1845
02:31:09,721 --> 02:31:11,622
Madam President and council members.

1846
02:31:13,043 --> 02:31:15,565
I am Maurice Edward Vincent, superintendent of schools.

1847
02:31:15,725 --> 02:31:31,115
I am here this evening to first represent the district and to say that the incident that took place yesterday is not something that we want to see repeated ever again in the Medford Public Schools.

1848
02:31:31,635 --> 02:31:38,580
I don't endorse or support any kind of weapons coming into the school that is not the Medford Public Schools

1849
02:31:38,947 --> 02:31:40,168
that I am here representing.

1850
02:31:40,568 --> 02:31:44,172
So what happened yesterday was a terrible, terrible incident.

1851
02:31:44,932 --> 02:31:48,015
It was not something that we knew was going to happen in advance.

1852
02:31:48,736 --> 02:31:54,240
And working with communications to get that message out and trying to keep the entire community safe.

1853
02:31:54,981 --> 02:31:57,263
Working collaboratively with the police, we had

1854
02:31:57,855 --> 02:32:03,378
many, many police officers on campus yesterday, and there was a lot of investigating happening.

1855
02:32:03,398 --> 02:32:11,202
There was a lot of information that as things were unfolding, we had to wait for more information to become available.

1856
02:32:11,723 --> 02:32:21,188
So I know that we had two medical emergencies yesterday, one earlier in the morning, which was a separate event, and then the second event that took place.

1857
02:32:22,108 --> 02:32:25,630
And that incident and all students that were involved

1858
02:32:26,105 --> 02:32:27,706
a significant number of students.

1859
02:32:28,926 --> 02:32:35,690
Again, looking at the video cameras and figuring out how many people were actually involved, it's a significant number.

1860
02:32:36,330 --> 02:32:38,551
We had plenty of police support today.

1861
02:32:38,971 --> 02:32:41,312
We also had fire support in the schools.

1862
02:32:42,093 --> 02:32:53,118
Our fire personnel, additional administrators were at the high school, teachers, staff, everyone, it was all hands on deck working together to keep the community safe.

1863
02:32:53,732 --> 02:32:56,113
We did have a higher absentee rate.

1864
02:32:56,554 --> 02:33:00,355
It wasn't 400 students, but we were in the high 200s today.

1865
02:33:00,996 --> 02:33:05,418
Normally we hover around 10% in terms of absence.

1866
02:33:07,059 --> 02:33:16,164
I am here today to just say that we are doing everything that we can do to address the situation that happened based on the students that are involved.

1867
02:33:16,764 --> 02:33:20,086
And because of the nature of yesterday's incident,

1868
02:33:20,841 --> 02:33:29,706
The police again are continuing their investigation at MPD and we are working collaboratively because it is an ongoing investigation.

1869
02:33:30,226 --> 02:33:35,369
And again, it was a significant number of students that were involved, others that were just bystanders.

1870
02:33:35,930 --> 02:33:45,475
And so that's the reason why there's been limited information because it's still an active, very active situation.

1871
02:33:46,556 --> 02:33:49,458
I do also want to report that we did have the opportunity

1872
02:33:50,422 --> 02:33:56,086
speak with the family today and with the student on campus.

1873
02:33:56,666 --> 02:34:09,854
And we are continuing to pray for his speedy recovery, but we are in communication and we are working collaboratively with the family as well.

1874
02:34:11,315 --> 02:34:15,018
My understanding that the student was relatively new student in the school transfer student.

1875
02:34:15,038 --> 02:34:16,339
That's my understanding.

1876
02:34:17,469 --> 02:34:21,192
It is a vocational student in one of our programs.

1877
02:34:21,212 --> 02:34:21,452
Yes.

1878
02:34:21,612 --> 02:34:26,815
And do you feel as though this might be related to a bullying incident or something like that, an underlying bullying incident?

1879
02:34:27,056 --> 02:34:35,561
What was the basis of the argument, the series of events or event that gave cause to arise to such an action?

1880
02:34:35,841 --> 02:34:44,767
So again, that action was surprising to everyone based on some of what's been shown on some of the video footage.

1881
02:34:45,728 --> 02:34:46,849
We're not sure.

1882
02:34:48,200 --> 02:34:52,822
There were comments about other interactions happening at other times.

1883
02:34:53,482 --> 02:35:04,025
Since it is an active investigation, I have to be, I'm not able to say too much, but what I can say is it's an active investigation.

1884
02:35:04,425 --> 02:35:15,848
The police are deeply involved and any situation involving weapons, which are not allowed in schools, discipline is being meted out.

1885
02:35:16,295 --> 02:35:20,576
according to what is said in the law regarding any kind of weapon.

1886
02:35:20,996 --> 02:35:26,458
So I do want to say that it's not being taken lightly, it's being addressed appropriately.

1887
02:35:26,838 --> 02:35:42,802
And because of FERPA, I still need to be careful with what is said publicly on the floor, but what I can assure this body and the community that is listening is that it is being addressed and we are making sure that we have all of the individuals

1888
02:35:43,387 --> 02:35:46,388
that were involved or were bystanders.

1889
02:35:48,668 --> 02:35:49,728
Thank you.

1890
02:35:49,868 --> 02:35:53,589
Could the student that stabbed the other student actually be let back into school?

1891
02:35:54,369 --> 02:35:55,469
Not according to the law.

1892
02:35:56,690 --> 02:35:59,230
Is it the intention of the school administration to expel that student?

1893
02:35:59,250 --> 02:36:00,350
We are following the law, yes.

1894
02:36:00,730 --> 02:36:03,511
Any kind of weapon that's- You're going to expel the kid.

1895
02:36:03,571 --> 02:36:04,731
We follow the law.

1896
02:36:04,871 --> 02:36:05,151
Yes.

1897
02:36:05,171 --> 02:36:06,872
I'm asking if the kid's getting expelled.

1898
02:36:08,472 --> 02:36:08,672
May I?

1899
02:36:10,038 --> 02:36:11,138
So thank you.

1900
02:36:11,158 --> 02:36:12,919
I'm Melanie McLaughlin.

1901
02:36:12,959 --> 02:36:13,859
I'm a school committee member.

1902
02:36:13,879 --> 02:36:19,681
I'm also a parent of three, two Medford high school graduates, one current Medford public school student.

1903
02:36:20,281 --> 02:36:33,086
I've lived in Medford for 23 years and I'm here tonight specifically because I want to support the superintendent in her role and because I want to support the school committee and the parents and families and students in the city.

1904
02:36:33,906 --> 02:36:37,447
We're all heartbroken about what has happened to our children.

1905
02:36:37,913 --> 02:36:41,334
or the past few months, but it has not been just the past few months.

1906
02:36:41,414 --> 02:36:45,856
And there are plenty of people in the community that know that and that understand that it has been years.

1907
02:36:46,356 --> 02:36:47,496
We've had a bullying problem.

1908
02:36:47,556 --> 02:36:49,177
Most high schools have bullying problems.

1909
02:36:49,197 --> 02:36:50,857
There's a rise in violence.

1910
02:36:51,277 --> 02:36:51,978
It's national.

1911
02:36:52,038 --> 02:36:53,298
You can see it all over the country.

1912
02:36:53,818 --> 02:36:58,740
It is happening, particularly because of pandemic, but also because of the politicized nature

1913
02:36:59,162 --> 02:37:03,464
of the hatred that exists in communities between polarized sides.

1914
02:37:03,865 --> 02:37:07,006
And our children are often mimicking what they're seeing their adults do.

1915
02:37:07,447 --> 02:37:18,753
And what I think is really important is what we've heard from city council members who are talking about finding solutions to work together, to collaborate, to change systems for all of our children, not some of our children, all of our children.

1916
02:37:19,053 --> 02:37:19,853
This has been ongoing.

1917
02:37:19,873 --> 02:37:24,976
We're talking about not just the past four years of this administration, meaning this particular superintendent.

1918
02:37:25,316 --> 02:37:28,198
This has been an ongoing problem from when other people were on school committee.

1919
02:37:28,580 --> 02:37:30,361
from when people have been around for some time.

1920
02:37:30,381 --> 02:37:33,422
I want to clarify for the community and for city counselors.

1921
02:37:34,902 --> 02:37:36,663
I'm not afraid of being yelled at.

1922
02:37:37,203 --> 02:37:38,083
I just don't like it.

1923
02:37:38,443 --> 02:37:40,584
I think it's inappropriate and unprofessional.

1924
02:37:41,244 --> 02:37:50,207
And when we talk about bullying in our community, I have never seen more of an example of bullying in our community that I see in the city council chambers every single week.

1925
02:37:51,951 --> 02:37:54,433
And I think that everybody in the community would agree with that.

1926
02:37:54,513 --> 02:37:55,314
Point of information.

1927
02:37:55,494 --> 02:37:57,936
There's a difference between bullying and passion.

1928
02:37:58,277 --> 02:37:59,918
And that's what you lack, ma'am.

1929
02:37:59,938 --> 02:38:01,920
You lack the passion.

1930
02:38:03,121 --> 02:38:04,922
I think we both know each other well, George.

1931
02:38:04,942 --> 02:38:05,803
We're all neighbors here.

1932
02:38:05,843 --> 02:38:06,624
We all know each other.

1933
02:38:07,184 --> 02:38:08,045
We all know each other.

1934
02:38:08,446 --> 02:38:10,027
Our children play together.

1935
02:38:10,087 --> 02:38:13,150
If you could please continue through the chair.

1936
02:38:13,210 --> 02:38:14,331
Great choice of support.

1937
02:38:19,887 --> 02:38:23,308
So the ongoing bullying is inappropriate and is what our children are seeing.

1938
02:38:23,668 --> 02:38:25,589
And that's what I would like to specifically point out.

1939
02:38:25,969 --> 02:38:31,450
We wanna figure out how to work, should collaborate together to change outcomes for all children.

1940
02:38:31,830 --> 02:38:36,571
And I'm not gonna be shamed, I'm not gonna be blamed and I'm not gonna be named and neither should any of us.

1941
02:38:37,011 --> 02:38:43,393
And I would ask that our city council members across the board and that our community across the board stand up to bullies everywhere.

1942
02:38:44,033 --> 02:38:47,134
And we make sure that this stops in our community and in our schools.

1943
02:38:48,138 --> 02:38:51,240
And I'm here to do that, and I'm here to roll up my sleeves and help make sure that that happens.

1944
02:38:51,560 --> 02:38:53,141
And I think we all should be doing that.

1945
02:38:54,181 --> 02:38:54,482
Thank you.

1946
02:38:55,642 --> 02:38:58,444
Point of information, Madam President.

1947
02:38:58,744 --> 02:39:05,848
Madam Superintendent, yesterday a young man came to the podium and addressed the situation that happened.

1948
02:39:06,628 --> 02:39:11,511
Did you hear the young man who described a very similar situation just a few weeks prior?

1949
02:39:12,872 --> 02:39:13,993
I asked the superintendent.

1950
02:39:14,293 --> 02:39:14,453
Yes.

1951
02:39:17,078 --> 02:39:18,058
Was that addressed today?

1952
02:39:18,459 --> 02:39:28,062
Did you contact the guidance counselor that he talked to, to express the concern of the same people threatening him to stab him?

1953
02:39:28,543 --> 02:39:30,123
Did you address that today?

1954
02:39:31,484 --> 02:39:37,706
That specific comment that was made yesterday, it's still being under investigation.

1955
02:39:37,806 --> 02:39:45,089
And there's another, there are other things that have come forward, which are also being fully investigated.

1956
02:39:48,257 --> 02:39:48,697
Thank you.

1957
02:39:49,958 --> 02:39:51,799
Thank you.

1958
02:39:52,860 --> 02:39:55,782
Thank you, Madam Superintendent.

